CHANDIGARH ADMINISTRATION CHANDIGARH HOUSING BOARD 8, Jan Marg, Sector 9-D, Chandigarh Dated ; 14.05.2021 PRESS RELEASE E-Permit : Oxygen Cylinder for Home The Chandigarh Administration has taken note of the problem being faced by the patients who have been prescribed oxygen at home but they are finding it difficult to get oxygen cylinders from the market. Now the Chandigarh Administration, with the assistance of National Informatics Centre (NIC), has developed a facility where the patients may obtain online e-permit for Oxygen Cylinder. Application for e-permit may be submitted on the website of the Chandigarh Administration from 11.00 am on 15.05.2021 onwards. http://chandigarh.gov.in/health_covid19.htm 2. The following documents are required to be uploaded at the time of making the application: a) Prescription of the Doctor for requirement of oxygen b) Any address proof of Chandigarh 3. Once the application is approved, the applicant will get an intimation, The approval will be valid for two days. Though e-permit may be downloaded from the website yet hard copy is not required and the cylinder (maximum two) may be obtained even on the basis of the approved application number, from the following address: M/s Super Agencies, 40-MW Industrial Area-1 , Chandigarh- 160002 (Mobile No. 9888035000) (E-Mail: superchandigarh@gmail,com| 4, The Charges for Oxygen Cylinders by M/s Super Agencies are as under: a) If having empty Cylinder: ¢ Refilling charges @ Rs. 295/- plus 12% GST, for each 'D' Cylinder. b) If not having empty cylinder: « Refilling charges @ Rs. 295/- plus 12% GST, for each 'D' Cylinder « Security @ Rs. 25,000/- for each empty Cylinder which will be refunded after deduction of rent @ Rs. 100/- per day Ht L- J Yo 204} (Yashp: oan aS ' CEO, Chandigarh Housing Board Nodal Officer for Oxygen Supplies in UT Chandigarh Page Lof 1

Drive-through COVID vaccination for the 2nd dose of #Covishield (45+ age group) at DLF City Centre Mall Gurugram, tomorrow i.e. 14 May 2021 from 10 am onwards. 200 slots will be available, on a first come first serve basis

Drive-through COVID vaccination for the 2nd dose of #Covishield (45+ age group) at DLF City Centre Mall Gurugram, tomorrow i.e. 14 May 2021 from 10 am onwards. 200 slots will be available, on a first come first serve basis

9 CHANDIGARH, INDIA Naina Mishra Tribune News Service Chandigarh, May 12 The beneficiaries of the new age group (18-45 years) can book a slot from Thursday and obtain the time and place of vaccination through the CoWIN portal. The slots can be booked from 3 pm onwards, officials said. Dr Amandeep Kaur Kang, Director, Health Services, UT, said, “The slots for booking online appointment will be available tomorrow and remain open for the next 15 days. Initially, about 1,000 slots will be visible per day. Depending on the response, the slots may be increased later.” The Central Government has allotted 33,000 vaccines to the UT for persons in the age group of 18-45 years, The consignment of Covishield was received by the UT health authorities today. Eligible beneficiaries will be inoculated from May 14, Walk-in vaccination facility will not be available to the beneficiaries under this age group.
